Summary: 5 lights in boomerang-shape passed thru Cassiopeia on heading to Saturn was silent w/o blinking nav lights. No aircraft in area. Moved exceedingly fast. to south/east.
divs: sighting details1. was placing recyleables into bin--in my back yard-- when i looked up to south-west sky and noticed satellite progressing north. looked to cassiopeia for other possible south-heading satellites as the night is cloudless. 2. noted the very rapid speed, no blinking of nav lights, and was silent. its 5 lights were blurred \ hazy, but plainly observable. 3. initially thought it was an aircraft, but was not exhibiting colored\ blinking nav lights. positioning of 5 lights on object showed a sweep of more than 40 degrees from tip light to either tip. i thought it unusual in shape unlike commercial aircraft wing sweep. 4. 5 lights arraged in a boomerang shape, proceeded south-east at a very rapid, constant speed, without blinking nav lights, and was blurred--somewhat--as if to mask or lessen its observability. 5. chills 6. line of sight was obscured by neighbors' large cedar tree.
